d valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Soloing alligators in CT</span><hr size=1> I am currently a level 29 DE mage on firiona Vie server (RP server). I am trying to obtain pieces for my focus item. Currently I have my fire and air pet.<br>
<br>
On this server, CT is usually empty. I can't group with lights because of certain restriction to the server. My only two options is to wait for a dark to come by (which would be a long time) or try to solo the mob.<br>
<br>
I tried once with a fire pet, but it didn't work out. Pet died and had to zone.<br>
<br>
With air pet, I was able to kill it, but had no mana left over and pet almost dead. Fight was to close to my liking.<br>
<br>
Can anyone give me any useful tips to solo this camp? Should I try to level a bit more. Note, the server is under TLC on all zones, so I need to be in level range of the mob in order to loot it.<br>
<br>
Thank you in advance for the help.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ustiky.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stiky</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/01 1:43:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing alligators in CT</span><hr size=1> I'd suggest waiting a few levels or convincing someone to come down to help.  <br>
<br>
The alligators ROAM the hallway and you will get adds quite often unless you have the spawn broken.<br>
<br>
I know you can get experience down there at 30 and 31.<br>
<br>
The magicians in Najena also drop the items and najena would be closer to your home base.  I'm not sure what level they are as I've never hunted them, but you might want to look into them.  They MIGHT be easier, those alligators hit HARD! <p>Stiky Fyngers Halfing Rogue<BR>
Peat - Halfling Druid<BR>
Jorlaan - Barbarian Shaman<BR>
Sumlain - High Elf Paladin<BR>
Nydara - Dark Elf Enchanter<BR>
Biktil - Gnome Mage<BR>
Bristlebane<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucobeeblazesummoner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cobee Blazesummoner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of The Elements</span><br>  Posts: 205<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/01 2:03:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing alligators in CT</span><hr size=1> I never could solo gators; they add too often because they wander freely.  I agree with the above poster. <p><center><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=39942"><img src=http://roxorzjoo.homestead.com/files/sig.gif border=no></a><br><i>Magi and CoH biznatch of the 58th re-ding</i><br><br><b>Conscience</b><br>Druid of Hibernia<br><i>Seraphic Malice</i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umohorat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mo ho rat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/01 4:01:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing alligators in CT</span><hr size=1> /ooc<br>
<br>
I too play a mage on the FV server.<br>
<br>
And I too tried to solo alligators in CT.<br>
At 29 without success.<br>
I returned at 34, alas still no success.<br>
<br>
At 37 I again returned, and I grouped with some people hunting alligators (mage, cleric, druid and me).<br>
Even if some of the alligators were green to me, we still had to zone out once and some fights were really close.<br>
<br>
The problem are the above mentioned roaming alligators.<br>
If your pet is fighting already two or three and another one decides to aggro on you, you have to zone, no way around it, fight is over.<br>
<br>
You best chance is the single alligator, that sometimes spawns at entrance and then wanders through the tunnel into the courtyard. Happens ever 20 minutes or so. I got two torn pages of this one.<br>
<br>
For the mages in Najena you are most likely too high meanwhile. Check it out, maybe some are still lightblue to you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Maleph Spidersoul</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usrial.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Srial</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/01 4:19:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing alligators in CT</span><hr size=1> At 29 I desperately tried to break the spawn in the hallway between the green and blue pools 4 times, and finally managed to hold the hallway by myself for about 4 spawn rotations (that's what 24 minutes?)   At that point 2 of them spawned on top of me and overwhelmed my fire pet with me healing it as fast as I could.  I got 1 torch in that time.  Considering all 4 of my attempts ended up with me trying desperately to gate out with at least 1, often 2 gators trying to kill me I don't really recommend this.<br>
<br>
At 35 I came back and had a friend (a level 54 warrior) break the spawn for me killing each of the 3 gators about a minute apart.  I was then able to hold the hallway on my own with a focused water pet (I bought the stein) for 5 hours.  (I got the broom, 3 torches and all my torn pages of mastery but still no #@#$! shovel).  I'm convinced with a bit of luck at 35 I could break the spawn if I was very careful.  Maybe a 50/50 shot.  Once it was broken and they were spaced a little, holding it isn't much problem.   Oh, I never got that ring of Evolouy thing either, it must be real, real rare.<br>
<br>
I recommend camping in the middle of the hallway, that way you have plenty of time to nuke runners.   The one time the camp went to heck in those 5 hours was when a runner fully resisted my blaze twice on it's way to the blue pool.  Then I had to gate, but was able to get back and gain control of the hallway before the other 2 gators spawned.<br>
<br>
The single spawn at the entrance is definately doable, but boring as heck as you have to sit and stare at the floor to make sure you catch it before it runs into the complex.   I went insane after doing that about 15 minutes and didn't see a single one.  Every time I'm not looking for it and don't have a pet up, though, I always see it by the entrance, so Murphy's law applies to alligators, too.<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
<br>
Srial Elemaster - 37th level Magician  Morrel Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxreynnx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>x Reynn x</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/01 5:37:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing alligators in CT</span><hr size=1> Thank you all for your suggestions.  I was lucky enough to find a group last night to do gators.  All I need now is the shovel.<br>
<br>
One of the drawbacks is that Verant added TLC to include quest items as well.  Najena would be a viable option, but the mages that I know of are already green to me, so no magic drops.  I am sure there are other mages that may still give me exp, but I don't know the zone at all, and I am not sure if I can work my way down there to kill them.<br>
<br>
Hopefully I will be able to find another group in CT tonight to finish up the quest.<br>
<br>
Thanks again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukakarrot54.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kakarrot54</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#333333>(12/4/01 12:20:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing alligators in CT</span><hr size=1> One Shock of Spikes kills the mages in Najena (partial resists, which were rare, showed their hp to be something about 160); I nailed em before they even summonned their pet =)  Most things are green in there at 25, the only things that are blue (I only went deep enough to camp the first two mages) are Tentacle Terrors and &quot;a skeleton&quot; which is blue but fights like a yelow at that level.  It should be simple for a 29 mage to solo here, but very boring, as the mages are on a long spawn timer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxreynnx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>x Reynn x</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(12/7/01 2:39:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing alligators in CT</span><hr size=1> The only problem with killing greens is that I will not get anything due to TLC.  At level 24, I was able to kill some greens and not have TLC take effect but on others it would. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub1